			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&gt; Wow wow, so much work is being done to speed up TLS access in the
&gt; IRT. Does anybody have performance data to justify it?

No. :-)  The main motivation is really to move the %gs segment so that we can use "jmp *%gs:8" to implement a sigreturn-style set-all-registers-and-jump operation for the debug stub.  Using %gs:4 for the IRT's TLS is just a side benefit that I might as well implement.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-07-24T15:20:58.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-07-24T15:20:58.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 12 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2881#c12" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2881/comments/full/12" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>